ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now let me create the profile steps file. This is going to be a large
file. I need to implement steps for all profile scenarios. Let me think carefull
y about what each step should do.\n\nThe steps need to make actual HTTP requests
and assert on responses. Since we\'re using mocked repositories, I need to mock 
the repo responses before each request.\n\nLet me organize the context and helpe
rs first, then define all the steps.\n\nKey observations:\n- `ProfileService.cre
ateProfile` checks for existing profile with `profileRepo.findOne`\n- `ProfileSe
rvice.updateProfile` checks for existing profile\n- `ProfileService.getProfile` 
returns profile + photos\n- `ProfileService.addPhoto` checks photo count, create
s photo, and if `is_avatar=true`, updates profile avatar_url\n- `ProfileService.
reorderPhotos` uses `dataSource.transaction`\n- `ProfileService.deletePhoto` use
s `photoRepo.softDelete` then reorders via `dataSource.transaction`\n\nFor `data
Source.transaction`, my mock in `bdd-setup.js` now supports it. But the actual `
ProfileService` calls `dataSource.transaction(async (manager) => { ... manager.u
pdate(...) })`. My mock should handle this.\n\nFor `photoRepo.softDelete`, TypeO
RM\'s `softDelete` takes criteria like `{ id: photoId, user_id: userId }`. In my
mock, it just resolves.\n\nFor `reorderPhotos`, after the transaction, `ProfileS
ervice` does `this.photoRepo.find({ where: { user_id: userId, deleted_at: null }
, order: { sort_order: "ASC" } })`.\n\nWait, the `ProfileService.deletePhoto` do
es:\n1. `photoRepo.findOne` to find the photo\n2. `photoRepo.softDelete({ id: ph
otoId, user_id: userId })`\n3. `photoRepo.find({ where: { user_id: userId, delet
ed_at: null }, order: { sort_order: "ASC" } })`\n4. `dataSource.transaction` wit
h `manager.update`\n\nBut since `photoRepo` is mocked, `softDelete` doesn\'t act
ually modify anything. So in the mock, after `softDelete`, when `photoRepo.find`
is called, it will return whatever the mock is set to return. I need to set up t
he mocks appropriately in the step definitions.\n\nActually, mocking at the BDD 
level is quite tricky because each step needs to set up the right mocks for the 
next HTTP request. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nFor `createProfile
` tests:\n- Mock `profileRepo.findOne` to return `null` (no existing profile)\n-
After the request, `profileRepo.create` and `profileRepo.save` are called\n\nFor
`updateProfile` tests:\n- Mock `profileRepo.findOne` to return an existing profi
le\n- After the request, `profileRepo.update` is called\n\nFor `getProfile` test
s:\n- Mock `profileRepo.findOne` to return a profile\n- Mock `photoRepo.find` to
return photos\n\nFor `addPhoto` tests:\n- Mock `photoRepo.count` to return curre
nt count\n- Mock `photoRepo.create` to return the photo object\n- If `is_avatar=
true`, `profileRepo.update` is called\n\nFor `reorderPhotos` tests:\n- Mock `pho
toRepo.find` to return photos with IDs\n- The transaction mock handles `manager.
update`\n- Then `photoRepo.find` is called again to get updated photos\n\nFor `d
eletePhoto` tests:\n- Mock `photoRepo.findOne` to return the photo\n- `photoRepo
.softDelete` is mocked\n- Mock `photoRepo.find` to return remaining photos\n- Th
e transaction mock handles `manager.update`\n\nThis is definitely doable but req
uires careful mock setup in each step.\n\nLet me write the `profile.steps.js` fi
le. I\'ll create a shared context object like in `auth-common.js`.\n\nActually, 
I realize that for some steps (like photo reorder/delete), the mocks need to be 
set up in the `When` step, and then assertions made in the `Then` step. But sinc
e the HTTP request has already been made in the `When` step, the assertions need
to check the response or the mock calls.\n\nLet me write a comprehensive `profil
e.steps.js`.\n\nOne more thing - for steps about "the app should redirect the us
er to profile setup" or "the user should enter the home screen", these are mobil
e app behaviors. In the API BDD context, I\'ll assert on API response fields tha
t would trigger these app behaviors. For example:\n- `is_complete = true` would 
allow home screen\n- `is_new_user = true` would trigger profile setup\n\nActuall
y, looking at the auth BDD, `auth-common.js` has:\n```js\naliasThenAnd(\'the use
r should be redirected to profile setup\', () => {\n  assert.strictEqual(context
.response.body.data.is_new_user, true);\n});\n```\n\nSo I can use similar patter
ns for Profile BDD.\n\nLet me write the profile steps now.',
    encrypted=None
)
