    type='think',
    think='The issue is that `autoBindSteps` is not finding all the step definit
ions because some step texts in the feature files use `"` quotes while my step d
efinitions use different patterns. Also, `jest-cucumber`\'s `autoBindSteps` requ
ires exact string matching or regex matching.\n\nLooking at the errors:\n- `the 
user uploads an avatar, enters nickname "Alice"...` - in my profile-step-defs.js
, I have the exact string `when(\'the user uploads an avatar, enters nickname "A
lice", selects gender "female", enters birth_date "1998-05-20", and allows locat
ion access\'...` which should match.\n- `the API should reject any matching-rela
ted requests with code 1000` - I have `aliasThenAnd(\'the API should reject any 
matching-related requests with code 1000\'...` which should match.\n- `the user 
selects a JPG image within 10MB as avatar` - I have `when(\'the user selects a J
PG image within 10MB as avatar\'...` which should match.\n\nWait, the error says
"Scenario has 4 step(s) in the feature file, but 2 step definition(s) defined." 
This means `autoBindSteps` is only finding 2 of the step definitions, not all of
them. \n\nThe problem is likely that `autoBindSteps` from `jest-cucumber` only l
ooks at step definition functions that are directly defined in the passed module
s, and it matches them by the step text. But `aliasThenAnd` registers steps with
both `then` and `and` - maybe `autoBindSteps` has trouble with duplicate registr
ations?\n\nActually, looking at the `auth-common.js` pattern, they also use `ali
asThenAnd` and it works with `autoBindSteps` there. Wait, no - `auth-common.js` 
is used with `autoBindSteps` in `auth_login_*.steps.js` files. Let me check one 
of those.\n\nActually, looking at `auth.steps.js`, it uses `defineFeature` direc
tly, not `autoBindSteps`. The `auth_login_*.steps.js` files use `autoBindSteps(f
eature, [commonSteps])`. So `commonSteps` must work with `autoBindSteps`.\n\nThe
key difference might be that `common.js` uses `aliasThenAnd` with both `then` an
d `and`, and `autoBindSteps` somehow handles it. But in my `profile-step-defs.js
`, I defined `aliasThenAnd` inside the exported function. This should work the s
ame way.\n\nWait, let me look more carefully at the error. It says "2 step defin
ition(s) defined" for a scenario with 4 steps. The 2 step definitions found are 
probably the `Given` and `When` steps. The `Then` and `And` steps are not being 
found. Why?\n\nOh! I think I see the issue. In `profile-step-defs.js`, I defined
:\n```js\nthen(\'the profile should be marked as complete\', () => { ... });\nan
d(\'the user should enter the home screen\', () => { ... });\n```\n\nBut `autoBi
ndSteps` might not handle `and` steps properly when they\'re defined separately 
from `then`. Looking at `auth-common.js`, they use `aliasThenAnd` which register
s with BOTH `then` and `and` for the same pattern. But for `and` steps that don\
't have a corresponding `then` with the same text, they might not be found.\n\nA
ctually wait, `jest-cucumber`\'s `autoBindSteps` should find steps registered wi
th `and` just like `then`. Let me check the `jest-cucumber` documentation or beh
avior.\n\nThe issue might be simpler: `autoBindSteps` looks for step definitions
by matching the step text from the feature file against the patterns passed to `
given`, `when`, `then`, `and`. If the pattern is a string, it does exact matchin
g. But maybe the feature file has slightly different text?\n\nLet me re-read the
feature file for `profile_complete_minimum_profile.feature`:\n```\n    When the 
user uploads an avatar, enters nickname "Alice", selects gender "female", enters
birth_date "1998-05-20", and allows location access\n    Then the profile should
be marked as complete\n    And the user should enter the home screen\n```\n\nAnd
my step definitions:\n```js\n  when(\'the user uploads an avatar, enters nicknam
e "Alice", selects gender "female", enters birth_date "1998-05-20", and allows l
ocation access\', async () => { ... });\n  aliasThenAnd(\'the profile should be 
marked as complete\', () => { ... });\n  aliasThenAnd(\'the user should enter th
e home screen\', () => { ... });\n```\n\nWait, `aliasThenAnd` registers with `th
en` AND `and`. So `then(\'the profile should be marked as complete\', ...)` and 
`and(\'the profile should be marked as complete\', ...)` are both registered. Bu
t the feature file has `Then the profile should be marked as complete` and `And 
the user should enter the home screen`. So `then` should match the first, and `a
nd` should match the second. But why is autoBindSteps saying only 2 step definit
ions are defined?\n\nOh! I think I found the issue. `autoBindSteps` might be cou
nting the number of unique step definitions found across ALL scenarios in the fe
ature. If there are steps that appear in multiple scenarios but aren\'t defined,
it might fail differently. But the error message specifically says "Scenario X h
as 4 step(s) in the feature file, but 2 step definition(s) defined."\n\nLet me t
hink about this differently. Maybe `autoBindSteps` has a bug or limitation with 
how it counts steps when `and` is used. Or maybe the `and` function passed to th
e step definition module is not the same `and` that `autoBindSteps` uses for mat
ching.\n\nActually, looking at the jest-cucumber source, `autoBindSteps` creates
its own `given`, `when`, `then`, `and` functions that track which steps are defi
ned. When it calls the step definition module, it passes these tracking function
s. The `then` and `and` functions are separate trackers. If I use `aliasThenAnd`
to call both `then` and `and` with the same pattern, it registers the step twice
- once in `then` tracker and once in `and` tracker. For a `Then` step in the fea
ture, it looks in the `then` tracker. For an `And` step, it looks in the `and` t
racker.\n\nSo if I define `then(\'the profile should be marked as complete\', ..
.)` and `and(\'the user should enter the home screen\', ...)` separately, it sho
uld work. But I\'m using `aliasThenAnd` for both, which means:\n- `aliasThenAnd(
\'the profile should be marked as complete\', ...)` registers in BOTH `then` and
`and` trackers\n- `aliasThenAnd(\'the user should enter the home screen\', ...)`
registers in BOTH `then` and `and` trackers\n\nThis should still work because wh
en `autoBindSteps` looks for the `Then` step, it finds it in the `then` tracker.
When it looks for the `And` step, it finds it in the `and` tracker.\n\nBut wait 
- `aliasThenAnd` also registers `then(\'the user should enter the home screen\',
...)` which might conflict if there\'s a scenario that uses `Then the user shoul
d enter the home screen` instead of `And`. That\'s fine though.\n\nLet me check 
if maybe `autoBindSteps` is case-sensitive or whitespace-sensitive. No, the stri
ngs look identical.\n\nHmm, let me look at the actual `profile_complete_minimum_
profile.steps.js` file to make sure the import is correct.',
