c that checks profile completeness in the mock setup, the request succeeds with 
code 0 (or whatever the matching service returns).\n\nI have two options:\n- Cha
nge the assertion to expect the request to succeed (since the guard is mocked)\n
- Or change the mock to make the guard reject for this scenario\n\nSince the BDD
test is about verifying the guard behavior, I should update the `bdd-setup.js` t
o allow the `ProfileCompletionGuard` mock to be configurable per-test, or I can 
mock it differently in the step definition.\n\nActually, looking at the step def
inition:\n```js\n  when(\'the user sends a swipe request via API\', async () => 
