ion:\n```js\n  then(\'the API should return code 1000\', () => {\n    assert.str
ictEqual(context.response.body.code, 1000);\n  });\n```\n\nSince the guard is mo
cked to always return true, this will fail. I can either:\n1. Change the mock gu
ard to actually check profile completeness\n2. Change the assertion to check som
ething else\n\nI think option 1 is better because it makes the BDD test more mea
ningful. Let me update `bdd-setup.js` to make `ProfileCompletionGuard` check pro
